87
00:05:56,359 --> 00:05:58,710
When I asked...

88
00:06:00,390 --> 00:06:04,720
My mom for money to buy snacks, I was jittery.

89
00:06:04,720 --> 00:06:07,689
Me too. So I wasn't willing to go back,

90
00:06:07,689 --> 00:06:10,750
but to stay in Grandma Yun's house.

91
00:06:10,750 --> 00:06:12,700
How about your parents?

92
00:06:13,570 --> 00:06:15,350
They were busy.

93
00:06:27,760 --> 00:06:29,390
Are you All right?

94
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:33,560
- Your hair is in a mess.
- I'll fix it myself.

95
00:06:42,510 --> 00:06:45,949
I think the couple who was riding wildly must be in an ambiguous relationship.

96
00:06:45,949 --> 00:06:50,419
But they also might be two un-moral daredevils who ignored traffic safety.

97
00:06:50,419 --> 00:06:53,449
How do you know they aren't head over heels in love??

98
00:06:53,449 --> 00:06:58,169
Have you ever heard of an interesting psychological experiment, Drawbridge Effect?

99
00:06:58,169 --> 00:07:00,750
According to it, one's heart will beat faster despite itself

100
00:07:00,750 --> 00:07:03,130
when he crosses a suspension bridge in fear.

101
00:07:03,130 --> 00:07:07,440
If he happens to meet a girl, he will take it

102
00:07:07,440 --> 00:07:11,770
as a symbol of falling in love with her.

103
00:07:11,770 --> 00:07:14,379
So, what does it mean?

104
00:07:14,379 --> 00:07:18,269
It shows outer stimuli can quickly send two people into an emotional state.

105
00:07:18,269 --> 00:07:21,949
Dopamine will emerge in their bodies, making them in love.

106
00:07:21,949 --> 00:07:25,960
So, people in an ambiguous relationship will tend to choose some exciting activities

107
00:07:25,960 --> 00:07:28,889
when dating, such as watching horror movies,

108
00:07:28,889 --> 00:07:31,489
bungee jumping, and riding wildly like that.

109
00:07:31,489 --> 00:07:35,650
According to what you said, the essence of love is just a chemical reaction?

110
00:07:35,650 --> 00:07:37,479
Dopamine delivers a sense of falling in love;

111
00:07:37,479 --> 00:07:41,299
Phenylethylamine a sense of sweetness; Oxytocin a sense of dependence;

112
00:07:41,299 --> 00:07:44,850
noradrenaline a sense of being infatuated.

113
00:07:44,850 --> 00:07:46,790
Don't you think so?

114
00:07:46,790 --> 00:07:48,790
I have no conclusion.

115
00:07:48,790 --> 00:07:52,610
We're just exchanging ideas.

116
00:07:52,610 --> 00:07:55,000
On love?

117
00:07:56,880 --> 00:07:59,910
If so, let's go deeper into this theme.

118
00:07:59,910 --> 00:08:02,190
How about doing an experiment?

119
00:08:02,190 --> 00:08:04,040
- What?
- Drawbridge Effect.

120
00:08:04,040 --> 00:08:09,220
Let's see if we can fall in love with each other in a short time under outer stimuli.

121
00:08:09,220 --> 00:08:11,779
- How about watching a horror movie?
- Now?

122
00:08:11,779 --> 00:08:14,969
You major in psychology, and I major in psychiatry.

123
00:08:14,969 --> 00:08:18,990
We're perfectly suited to discuss this subject!

124
00:08:18,990 --> 00:08:21,110
- But…
- Let's watch this.

125
00:08:21,110 --> 00:08:22,670
What do you think?

126
